<h2 class="header"><i>1</i>Section 4.1<a class="headerlink" href="#section-41" name="section-41">&para;</a></h2>
<h3 class="header"><i>1.1</i>Question 1<a class="headerlink" href="#question-1" name="question-1">&para;</a></h3>
<blockquote>
<p>Determine a condition on <span>$|x-1|$</span> that will ensure that<br />
(a) <span>$|x^2-1| &lt; 1/2$</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><span>$|x^2-1| = |x-1||x+1|$</span>. If <span>$|x-1| &lt; 1$</span>, then <span>$|x| \leq 2$</span> so <span>$|x+1| \leq |x| + 1 \leq 3$</span>. Then <span>$|x^2-1| \leq 3|x-c|$</span>. Let <span>$\epsilon = 1/2$</span>. Then if <span>$|x-c| &lt; \epsilon/3$</span>, <span>$|x^2-1| \leq \epsilon = 1/2$</span>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>(b) <span>$|x^2-1| &lt; 1/10^3$</span> (I think there's a typo in my version - it says <span>$1/10^{-3}$</span> but that is strange notation)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>TBC</p>
<blockquote>
<p>(c) <span>$|x^2-1| &lt; 1/n$</span><br />
(d) <span>$|x^3-1| &lt; 1/n$</span></p>
</blockquote>
